<p>You're being oddly defensive about somebody else's opinion about somebody else's work. To clarify:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>It works when you read it for what it is</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I do not agree with this part. I am expressing why, and then explaining ways I feel the author could've <em>made</em> it work within what I perceive to be the boundaries of the piece. The conceit rings as false to me, because it is assuming a tension that I do not believe exists. Based on material culled from the tale, I'm articulating the possibility of a different sort of tension, one that I think falls well within its purview. No offense was meant, and I'm not sure why you're taking any.</p>

